# Express & Node.js — Routes & Services (Part 2)

## Route structure

- Keep route handlers **thin**. Business logic in services.
- One file per resource or route group; use `express.Router()` and mount: `app.use('/api/users', userRoutes)`.

## Route file (moduleName.route.js)

Define router with `mergeParams: true` if mounted under params (e.g. `/projects/:projectId/ai`). Use `router.use(authenticateUser)` and `validate(schema)` middleware.

```js
// modules/ai/ai.route.js
const express = require('express');
const router = express.Router({ mergeParams: true });
const authenticateUser = require('../../middleware/apiUserAuthenticate');
const validate = require('../../middleware/validationMiddleware');
const { generateTestCaseSchema } = require('./ai.schema');
const { generateTestCases } = require('./ai.controller');

router.use(authenticateUser);
router.post('/generateTestCase', validate(generateTestCaseSchema), generateTestCases);
module.exports = router;
```

**Schema file (moduleName.schema.js):** Export Zod (or Joi) schemas. Validation middleware runs `schema.safeParse(req.body)`; on failure returns BadRequestError with `.error.flatten()`.

**Rules:** One route file per module. Mount router in app (e.g. `app.use('/api/v1/projects/:projectId/ai', aiRoutes)`).

## Controller pattern

Export controller actions as `asyncHandler`-wrapped functions. Use request logger, try/catch, and **apiResponseTemplate** for all responses.

```js
// modules/ai/ai.controller.js
const asyncHandler = require('../../utils/asyncHandler');
const logger = require('../../logger');
const { SuccessResponse, NotFoundError, InternalServerError } = require('../../utils/apiResponseTemplate');
const aiService = require('./ai.service');

exports.generateTestCases = asyncHandler(async (req, res) => {
  const reqLogger = logger.createRequestLogger(req);
  try {
    const responseData = await aiService.generateTestCases(req);
    return SuccessResponse(res, 'Test cases generated successfully', responseData);
  } catch (error) {
    reqLogger.error('Error generating test cases', error, { orgId: req.session?.user?.org_id });
    if (error.message === 'AI model not found or unauthorized') return NotFoundError(res, 'AI model not found');
    return InternalServerError(res, error);
  }
});
```

**Rules:** One exported function per route handler. In catch: log with context, map known errors to apiResponseTemplate, default `InternalServerError`.

## Service pattern

Services are **class-based**, hold business logic, export a **singleton instance**. Methods receive `req`; use `reqLogger.audit()` for start/success/fail. **Throw** errors with clear messages. Use **setImmediate** for non-blocking side effects; catch inside so they never affect the response.

```js
// modules/ai/ai.service.js
class AIService {
  async generateTestCases(req) {
    const reqLogger = logger.createRequestLogger(req);
    reqLogger.audit('GENERATE_TEST_CASES_START', req.session?.user, 'test_case_generation', { LLMId: req.body?.LLMId });
    const aiModel = await this.getAIModelByLLMId(req);
    // ... business logic
    reqLogger.audit('GENERATE_TEST_CASES_SUCCESS', req.session?.user, 'test_case_generation', { ... });
    return responseData;
  }
  logCostTrackingNonBlocking(req, usageInfo) {
    setImmediate(async () => {
      try { /* ... */ } catch (error) { logger.error('Failed to log cost tracking', error); }
    });
  }
}
module.exports = new AIService();
```

**Rules:** Export singleton: `module.exports = new AIService()`. Throw clear errors for controller to map.

## Input validation and sanitization

*Applies to both .ts and .js. Use Zod/Joi in either; omit type annotations in JS.*

- Validate **body, params, query**. Use Zod, Joi, or express-validator before business logic.
- Sanitize for XSS, SQL injection (parameterized queries only), path traversal.
- **Schema per route**: Define in **moduleName.schema.js**; use **validate(schema)** middleware; return 400 with validation errors on failure.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD - Zod
const createUserSchema = z.object({ email: z.string().email(), name: z.string().min(1).max(100) });
router.post('/users', asyncHandler(async (req, res) => {
  const parsed = createUserSchema.safeParse(req.body);
  if (!parsed.success) throw new ValidationError(parsed.error.flatten());
  const user = await userService.create(parsed.data);
  res.status(201).json({ success: true, data: user });
}));

// ❌ BAD - no validation
router.post('/users', async (req, res) => {
  const { email, name } = req.body;
  const user = await db.insert({ email, name });
  res.json(user);
});
```
